article.description: — Keegan Records scored 21 points and Colgate knocked off Lafayette 67-62 on Monday night for its 12th victory in a row.
article.headline: Records scores 21, Colgate takes down Lafayette 67-62 for 12th straight victory
article.linkText: Records scores 21, Colgate takes down Lafayette 67-62 for 12th straight victory
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- — Keegan Records scored 21 points and Colgate knocked off Lafayette 67-62 on Monday night for its 12th victory in a row. Records also had five rebounds for the Raiders (20-8, 14-1 Patriot League). Ryan Moffatt added 11 points while shooting 2 for 6 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 6 of 6 from the free throw line, and he also had five rebounds. Jalen Cox finished 4 of 5 from the floor to finish with nine points. The Leopards (11-17, 10-5) were led by Justin Vander Baan, who recorded 15 points, eight rebounds and three blocks. Devin Hines added 12 points for Lafayette. In addition, Kyle Jenkins had 10 points and seven rebounds. Colgate went into the half ahead of Lafayette 34-33. Records scored 13 points in the half. Moffatt scored a team-high nine points for Colgate in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
